762.question: How large are the improvements of the Attention-Sum Reader model when using the BookTest dataset?
762.response:
{'Image': 1, 'Rationale': 'Image 1 contains detailed information on the performance of the AS Reader model on the BookTest dataset, making it directly relevant to understanding the improvements.'}

The answer is: The AS Reader model achieves an accuracy of 78.4% on the named entity test and 85.7% on the common noun test when using the BookTest dataset. These results signify considerable improvements over other models and training datasets.
